{"id": 232041326, "title": "Jeremy Clarkson's partner says she had to 'raise her game' due to star's 'difficult' trait", "text": "Jeremy Clarkson's 'difficult' trait has resulted in his partner Lisa Hogan 'raising her game'. His Clarkson's Farm co-star said she was \"a sloth in comparison to him\" as his \"workaholic\" tendencies made him hard to live with. Lisa and Jeremy, 64, have been together since 2017 - and can also be seen working alongside each other in the hit Amazon Prime show. But she has admitted the relationship could be \"difficult\" at times due to the \"extraordinary\" amount he achieved in one day. The Mirror reports she said: \"He\u2019s a workaholic, and that can be difficult sometimes. I think I work quite hard, but I\u2019m like a sloth in comparison to him. He is extraordinary with the amount he can power through in one day.\" READ MORE: Michael Mosley's wife pays tribute to 'wonderful' husband as she says he 'nearly made it' She continued: \u201cHe was doing The Grand Tour, Who Wants to Be a Millionaire? and writing three columns a week, sometimes four. He has an extraordinary ability to get stuff done, so I\u2019ve had to raise my game a lot living with him. I would like to be a lot lazier, if I\u2019m being honest.\u201d Lisa joked the main inspiration for Jeremy's work ethic was \"not wanting to go back and live in the North of England\". She added: \"He\u2019s just one of those characters, but I think he wants to maintain his life.\u201d All three series of Clarkson's Farm are available to watch on Amazon Prime.", "summary": "His Clarkson's Farm co-star said she's 'a sloth in comparison to him'", "url": "https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/news/showbiz-tv/jeremy-clarksons-partner-says-raise-29322402", "image": "https://i2-prod.birminghammail.co.uk/incoming/article29151399.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/1_Clarksons-Farm-Photocall.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 15:32:33", "author": "James Brinsford,Kelly Ashmore", "authors": ["James Brinsford", "Kelly Ashmore"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": 0.392}